Q1: import java.util.*;  
    class UserInputDemo1  
    {  
    public static void main(String[] args)  
    {  
    Scanner sc= new Scanner(System.in); //System.in is a standard input stream  
    System.out.print("Enter a string: ");  
    String str= sc.nextLine();              //reads string   
    System.out.print("You have entered: "+str);             
    }  
    }  

Q2: The Java String class concat() method combines specified string at the end of this string. It returns a combined string. It is like appending another string.
    public class ConcatExample{    
    public static void main(String args[]){    
    String s1="java string";    
    s1.concat("is immutable");    
    System.out.println(s1);    
    s1=s1.concat(" is immutable so assign it explicitly");    
    System.out.println(s1);    
    }} 

Q3: To calculate the length of a string in Java, you can use an inbuilt length() method of the Java string class.
    Example: 
    class CalcLength {
        public static void main( String args[] ) {
           String name = "educative";  
           System.out.println("The length of the String \""+name+"\" is: " +length);    }
    }

